The article focuses on remittances, providing a snapshot for 2010 but also providing a summary of developments since "the turn of the millennium."  The information on "remittance corridors" as a percentage of GDP (2010) is especially interesting.  The Russia-Tajikstan corridor leads the way.  Remittances to GDP for Tajikistan was with 21.6% in 2010.  The the U.S., the largest corridor (in percent) is U.S.-Haiti.
